scientificName: Mimosa nuttallii (DC. ex Britton & Rose) B.L. Turner

morphospeciesIDRemarks: Thin woody stem. Woody all the way up to the top of stem. Leaves are glabrous except for short white hairs on the margins and underside of midvein. No veins clearly visible except for white midvein. Leaves spatulate in alternate arrangement. Leaves somewhat glaucous on underside.

morphospeciesIDRemarks: Alternate ovate/oblong leaves with pointed tip and double serrate margins. Woody sapling. Leaves glabrous on top. Leaves bottom side pubescent with tufts of hairs in vein axles. One main vein. Stem is hairy. Long stipples with axillary buds. Possibly Ostyra virginiana.
